2772/* Process the STORE_INFOs into the bitmaps into GEN and KILL. KILL
2773 may be NULL. */
2774
2775static void
2776scan_stores (store_info *store_info, bitmap gen, bitmap kill)
2777{
2778 while (store_info)
2779 {
2780 HOST_WIDE_INT i;
2781 group_info *group_info
2782 = rtx_group_vec[store_info->group_id];
2783 if (group_info->process_globally)
2784 for (i = store_info->begin; i < store_info->end; i++)
2785 {
2786 int index = get_bitmap_index (group_info, i);
2787 if (index != 0)
2788 {
2789 bitmap_set_bit (gen, index);
2790 if (kill)
2791 bitmap_clear_bit (kill, index);
2792 }
2793 }
2794 store_info = store_info->next;
2795 }
2796}

2798
2799/* Process the READ_INFOs into the bitmaps into GEN and KILL. KILL
2800 may be NULL. */
2801
2802static void
2803scan_reads (insn_info_t insn_info, bitmap gen, bitmap kill)
2804{
2805 read_info_t read_info = insn_info->read_rec;
2806 int i;
2807 group_info *group;
2808
2809 /* If this insn reads the frame, kill all the frame related stores. */
2810 if (insn_info->frame_read)
2811 {
2812 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (rtx_group_vec, i, group)
2813 if (group->process_globally && group->frame_related)
2814 {
2815 if (kill)
2816 bitmap_ior_into (kill, group->group_kill);
2817 bitmap_and_compl_into (gen, group->group_kill);
2818 }
2819 }
2820 if (insn_info->non_frame_wild_read)
2821 {
2822 /* Kill all non-frame related stores. Kill all stores of variables that
2823 escape. */
2824 if (kill)
2825 bitmap_ior_into (kill, kill_on_calls);
2826 bitmap_and_compl_into (gen, kill_on_calls);
2827 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (rtx_group_vec, i, group)
2828 if (group->process_globally && !group->frame_related)
2829 {
2830 if (kill)
2831 bitmap_ior_into (kill, group->group_kill);
2832 bitmap_and_compl_into (gen, group->group_kill);
2833 }
2834 }
2835 while (read_info)
2836 {
2837 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (rtx_group_vec, i, group)
2838 {
2839 if (group->process_globally)
2840 {
2841 if (i == read_info->group_id)
2842 {
2843 if (read_info->begin > read_info->end)
2844 {
2845 /* Begin > end for block mode reads. */
2846 if (kill)
2847 bitmap_ior_into (kill, group->group_kill);
2848 bitmap_and_compl_into (gen, group->group_kill);
2849 }
2850 else
2851 {
2852 /* The groups are the same, just process the
2853 offsets. */
2854 HOST_WIDE_INT j;
2855 for (j = read_info->begin; j < read_info->end; j++)
2856 {
2857 int index = get_bitmap_index (group, j);
2858 if (index != 0)
2859 {
2860 if (kill)
2861 bitmap_set_bit (kill, index);
2862 bitmap_clear_bit (gen, index);
2863 }
2864 }
2865 }
2866 }
2867 else
2868 {
2869 /* The groups are different, if the alias sets
2870 conflict, clear the entire group. We only need
2871 to apply this test if the read_info is a cselib
2872 read. Anything with a constant base cannot alias
2873 something else with a different constant
2874 base. */
2875 if ((read_info->group_id < 0)
2876 && canon_true_dependence (group->base_mem,
2877 GET_MODE (group->base_mem),
2878 group->canon_base_addr,
2879 read_info->mem, NULL_RTX))
2880 {
2881 if (kill)
2882 bitmap_ior_into (kill, group->group_kill);
2883 bitmap_and_compl_into (gen, group->group_kill);
2884 }
2885 }
2886 }
2887 }
2888
2889 read_info = read_info->next;
2890 }
2891}

2894/* Return the insn in BB_INFO before the first wild read or if there
2895 are no wild reads in the block, return the last insn. */
2896
2897static insn_info_t
2898find_insn_before_first_wild_read (bb_info_t bb_info)
2899{
2900 insn_info_t insn_info = bb_info->last_insn;
2901 insn_info_t last_wild_read = NULL;
2902
2903 while (insn_info)
2904 {
2905 if (insn_info->wild_read)
2906 {
2907 last_wild_read = insn_info->prev_insn;
2908 /* Block starts with wild read. */
2909 if (!last_wild_read)
2910 return NULL;
2911 }
2912
2913 insn_info = insn_info->prev_insn;
2914 }
2915
2916 if (last_wild_read)
2917 return last_wild_read;
2918 else
2919 return bb_info->last_insn;
2920}

2922
2923/* Scan the insns in BB_INFO starting at PTR and going to the top of
2924 the block in order to build the gen and kill sets for the block.
2925 We start at ptr which may be the last insn in the block or may be
2926 the first insn with a wild read. In the latter case we are able to
2927 skip the rest of the block because it just does not matter:
2928 anything that happens is hidden by the wild read. */
2929
2930static void
2931dse_step3_scan (basic_block bb)
2932{
2933 bb_info_t bb_info = bb_table[bb->index];
2934 insn_info_t insn_info;
2935
2936 insn_info = find_insn_before_first_wild_read (bb_info);
2937
2938 /* In the spill case or in the no_spill case if there is no wild
2939 read in the block, we will need a kill set. */
2940 if (insn_info == bb_info->last_insn)
2941 {
2942 if (bb_info->kill)
2943 bitmap_clear (bb_info->kill);
2944 else
2945 bb_info->kill = BITMAP_ALLOC (&dse_bitmap_obstack);
2946 }
2947 else
2948 if (bb_info->kill)
2949 BITMAP_FREE (bb_info->kill);
2950
2951 while (insn_info)
2952 {
2953 /* There may have been code deleted by the dce pass run before
2954 this phase. */
2955 if (insn_info->insn && INSN_P (insn_info->insn))
2956 {
2957 scan_stores (insn_info->store_rec, bb_info->gen, bb_info->kill);
2958 scan_reads (insn_info, bb_info->gen, bb_info->kill);
2959 }
2960
2961 insn_info = insn_info->prev_insn;
2962 }
2963}

2966/* Set the gen set of the exit block, and also any block with no
2967 successors that does not have a wild read. */
2968
2969static void
2970dse_step3_exit_block_scan (bb_info_t bb_info)
2971{
2972 /* The gen set is all 0's for the exit block except for the
2973 frame_pointer_group. */
2974
2975 if (stores_off_frame_dead_at_return)
2976 {
2977 unsigned int i;
2978 group_info *group;
2979
2980 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (rtx_group_vec, i, group)
2981 {
2982 if (group->process_globally && group->frame_related)
2983 bitmap_ior_into (bb_info->gen, group->group_kill);
2984 }
2985 }
2986}

2989/* Find all of the blocks that are not backwards reachable from the
2990 exit block or any block with no successors (BB). These are the
2991 infinite loops or infinite self loops. These blocks will still
2992 have their bits set in UNREACHABLE_BLOCKS. */
2993
2994static void
2995mark_reachable_blocks (sbitmap unreachable_blocks, basic_block bb)
2996{
2997 edge e;
2998 edge_iterator ei;
2999
3000 if (bitmap_bit_p (unreachable_blocks, bb->index))
3001 {
3002 bitmap_clear_bit (unreachable_blocks, bb->index);
3003 FOR_EACH_EDGE (e, ei, bb->preds)
3004 {
3005 mark_reachable_blocks (unreachable_blocks, e->src);
3006 }
3007 }
3008}

3010/* Build the transfer functions for the function. */
3011
3012static void
3013dse_step3 ()
3014{
3015 basic_block bb;
3016 sbitmap_iterator sbi;
3017 bitmap all_ones = NULL;
3018 unsigned int i;
3019
3020 auto_sbitmap unreachable_blocks (last_basic_block_for_fn (cfun));
3021 bitmap_ones (unreachable_blocks);
3022
3023 FOR_ALL_BB_FN (bb, cfun)
3024 {
3025 bb_info_t bb_info = bb_table[bb->index];
3026 if (bb_info->gen)
3027 bitmap_clear (bb_info->gen);
3028 else
3029 bb_info->gen = BITMAP_ALLOC (&dse_bitmap_obstack);
3030
3031 if (bb->index == ENTRY_BLOCK)
3032 ;
3033 else if (bb->index == EXIT_BLOCK)
3034 dse_step3_exit_block_scan (bb_info);
3035 else
3036 dse_step3_scan (bb);
3037 if (EDGE_COUNT (bb->succs) == 0)
3038 mark_reachable_blocks (unreachable_blocks, bb);
3039
3040 /* If this is the second time dataflow is run, delete the old
3041 sets. */
3042 if (bb_info->in)
3043 BITMAP_FREE (bb_info->in);
3044 if (bb_info->out)
3045 BITMAP_FREE (bb_info->out);
3046 }
3047
3048 /* For any block in an infinite loop, we must initialize the out set
3049 to all ones. This could be expensive, but almost never occurs in
3050 practice. However, it is common in regression tests. */
3051 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (unreachable_blocks, 0, i, sbi)
3052 {
3053 if (bitmap_bit_p (all_blocks, i))
3054 {
3055 bb_info_t bb_info = bb_table[i];
3056 if (!all_ones)
3057 {
3058 unsigned int j;
3059 group_info *group;
3060
3061 all_ones = BITMAP_ALLOC (&dse_bitmap_obstack);
3062 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (rtx_group_vec, j, group)
3063 bitmap_ior_into (all_ones, group->group_kill);
3064 }
3065 if (!bb_info->out)
3066 {
3067 bb_info->out = BITMAP_ALLOC (&dse_bitmap_obstack);
3068 bitmap_copy (bb_info->out, all_ones);
3069 }
3070 }
3071 }
3072
3073 if (all_ones)
3074 BITMAP_FREE (all_ones);
3075}

3079/*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3080 Fourth step.
3081
3082 Solve the bitvector equations.
3083----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3084
3085
3086/* Confluence function for blocks with no successors. Create an out
3087 set from the gen set of the exit block. This block logically has
3088 the exit block as a successor. */
3089
3090
3091
3092static void
3093dse_confluence_0 (basic_block bb)
3094{
3095 bb_info_t bb_info = bb_table[bb->index];
3096
3097 if (bb->index == EXIT_BLOCK)
3098 return;
3099
3100 if (!bb_info->out)
3101 {
3102 bb_info->out = BITMAP_ALLOC (&dse_bitmap_obstack);
3103 bitmap_copy (bb_info->out, bb_table[EXIT_BLOCK]->gen);
3104 }
3105}
3106
3107/* Propagate the information from the in set of the dest of E to the
3108 out set of the src of E. If the various in or out sets are not
3109 there, that means they are all ones. */
3110
3111static bool
3112dse_confluence_n (edge e)
3113{
3114 bb_info_t src_info = bb_table[e->src->index];
3115 bb_info_t dest_info = bb_table[e->dest->index];
3116
3117 if (dest_info->in)
3118 {
3119 if (src_info->out)
3120 bitmap_and_into (src_info->out, dest_info->in);
3121 else
3122 {
3123 src_info->out = BITMAP_ALLOC (&dse_bitmap_obstack);
3124 bitmap_copy (src_info->out, dest_info->in);
3125 }
3126 }
3127 return true;
3128}
3129
3130
3131/* Propagate the info from the out to the in set of BB_INDEX's basic
3132 block. There are three cases:
3133
3134 1) The block has no kill set. In this case the kill set is all
3135 ones. It does not matter what the out set of the block is, none of
3136 the info can reach the top. The only thing that reaches the top is
3137 the gen set and we just copy the set.
3138
3139 2) There is a kill set but no out set and bb has successors. In
3140 this case we just return. Eventually an out set will be created and
3141 it is better to wait than to create a set of ones.
3142
3143 3) There is both a kill and out set. We apply the obvious transfer
3144 function.
3145*/
3146
3147static bool
3148dse_transfer_function (int bb_index)
3149{
3150 bb_info_t bb_info = bb_table[bb_index];
3151
3152 if (bb_info->kill)
3153 {
3154 if (bb_info->out)
3155 {
3156 /* Case 3 above. */
3157 if (bb_info->in)
3158 return bitmap_ior_and_compl (bb_info->in, bb_info->gen,
3159 bb_info->out, bb_info->kill);
3160 else
3161 {
3162 bb_info->in = BITMAP_ALLOC (&dse_bitmap_obstack);
3163 bitmap_ior_and_compl (bb_info->in, bb_info->gen,
3164 bb_info->out, bb_info->kill);
3165 return true;
3166 }
3167 }
3168 else
3169 /* Case 2 above. */
3170 return false;
3171 }
3172 else
3173 {
3174 /* Case 1 above. If there is already an in set, nothing
3175 happens. */
3176 if (bb_info->in)
3177 return false;
3178 else
3179 {
3180 bb_info->in = BITMAP_ALLOC (&dse_bitmap_obstack);
3181 bitmap_copy (bb_info->in, bb_info->gen);
3182 return true;
3183 }
3184 }
3185}

3187/* Solve the dataflow equations. */
3188
3189static void
3190dse_step4 (void)
3191{
3192 df_simple_dataflow (DF_BACKWARD, NULL, dse_confluence_0,
3193 dse_confluence_n, dse_transfer_function,
3194 all_blocks, df_get_postorder (DF_BACKWARD),
3195 df_get_n_blocks (DF_BACKWARD));
3196 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3197 {
3198 basic_block bb;
3199
3200 fprintf (dump_file, "\n\n*** Global dataflow info after analysis.\n");
3201 FOR_ALL_BB_FN (bb, cfun)
3202 {
3203 bb_info_t bb_info = bb_table[bb->index];
3204
3205 df_print_bb_index (bb, dump_file);
3206 if (bb_info->in)
3207 bitmap_print (dump_file, bb_info->in, " in: ", "\n");
3208 else
3209 fprintf (dump_file, " in: *MISSING*\n");
3210 if (bb_info->gen)
3211 bitmap_print (dump_file, bb_info->gen, " gen: ", "\n");
3212 else
3213 fprintf (dump_file, " gen: *MISSING*\n");
3214 if (bb_info->kill)

3216 else

3221 fprintf (dump_file, " out: *MISSING*\n\n");
3222 }
3223 }
3224}

3228/*----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3229 Fifth step.
3230
3231 Delete the stores that can only be deleted using the global information.
3232----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3233
3234
3235static void
3236dse_step5 (void)
3237{
3238 basic_block bb;
3239 FOR_EACH_BB_FN (bb, cfun)
3240 {
3241 bb_info_t bb_info = bb_table[bb->index];
3242 insn_info_t insn_info = bb_info->last_insn;
3243 bitmap v = bb_info->out;
3244
3245 while (insn_info)
3246 {

3248 if (dump_file && insn_info->insn)
3249 {
3250 fprintf (dump_file, "starting to process insn %d\n",
3251 INSN_UID (insn_info->insn));
3252 bitmap_print (dump_file, v, " v: ", "\n");
3253 }
3254
3255 /* There may have been code deleted by the dce pass run before
3256 this phase. */
3257 if (insn_info->insn

3263

3265 deleted = true;

3283 fprintf (dump_file, "failing at i = %d\n", (int)i);
3284 deleted = false;
3285 break;
3286 }

3289 {
3290 if (dbg_cnt (dse)

3292 {

3294 insn_info->insn = NULL;
3295 globally_deleted++;
3296 }
3297 }
3298 }

3300 deleted. For instance, if the insn did a wild read, we
3301 no longer need to trash the info. */

3303 && INSN_P (insn_info->insn)
3304 && (!deleted))

3306 scan_stores (insn_info->store_rec, v, NULL);
3307 if (insn_info->wild_read)
3308 {

3318 {

3320 && !insn_info->frame_read)
3321 fprintf (dump_file, "regular read\n");
3322 if (insn_info->non_frame_wild_read)
3323 fprintf (dump_file, "non-frame wild read\n");
3324 if (insn_info->frame_read)
3325 fprintf (dump_file, "frame read\n");
3326 }
3327 scan_reads (insn_info, v, NULL);
3328 }
3329 }
3330
3331 insn_info = insn_info->prev_insn;
3332 }
3333 }
3334}

3422
3423static unsigned int
3424rest_of_handle_dse (void)
3425{
3426 df_set_flags (DF_DEFER_INSN_RESCAN);
3427
3428 /* Need the notes since we must track live hardregs in the forwards
3429 direction. */
3430 df_note_add_problem ();
3431 df_analyze ();
3432
3433 dse_step0 ();
3434 dse_step1 ();
3435 dse_step2_init ();
3436 if (dse_step2 ())
3437 {
3438 df_set_flags (DF_LR_RUN_DCE);
3439 df_analyze ();
3440 if (dump_file && (dump_flags & TDF_DETAILS))
3441 fprintf (dump_file, "doing global processing\n");
3442 dse_step3 ();
3443 dse_step4 ();
3444 dse_step5 ();
3445 }
3446
3447 dse_step6 ();
3448 dse_step7 ();
3449
3450 if (dump_file)
3451 fprintf (dump_file, "dse: local deletions = %d, global deletions = %d\n",
3452 locally_deleted, globally_deleted);
3453
3454 /* DSE can eliminate potentially-trapping MEMs.
3455 Remove any EH edges associated with them. */
3456 if ((locally_deleted || globally_deleted)
3457 && cfun->can_throw_non_call_exceptions
3458 && purge_all_dead_edges ())
3459 cleanup_cfg (0);
3460
3461 return 0;
3462}
